cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.NI 

This paper deals with security issues in public cloud infrastructure, specifically the vulnerability of multi-tenant environments to co-location attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
